============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Virtue Ethics
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Ethics is about developing virtuous character traits
Philosopher:  Aristotle
Example:      A courageous person acts courageously habitually; ethics is becoming good

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Central Bank
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government institution managing currency, money supply, interest rates
Formula:    Taylor Rule for interest rates
Economist:  John Taylor
Example:    US Federal Reserve raised rates to 5.25% in 2023 to fight inflation

Concept:    Game Theory
Category:   Economics
Definition: Study of strategic interactions between rational agents
Formula:    Nash equilibrium
Economist:  John Nash
Example:    OPEC cartel coordination; nuclear deterrence strategy

